34#import "modules/video_coding/codecs/h264/include/h264.h"

36#import "sdk/objc/components/video_codec/RTCVideoDecoderH264.h"
37#import "sdk/objc/components/video_codec/RTCVideoDecoderH265.h"
38#import "sdk/objc/components/video_codec/RTCVideoDecoderVTBVP9.h"
39
40@interface WK_RTCLocalVideoH264H265VP9Decoder : NSObject
41- (instancetype)initH264DecoderWithCallback:(webrtc::LocalDecoderCallback)callback;
42- (instancetype)initH265DecoderWithCallback:(webrtc::LocalDecoderCallback)callback;
43- (NSInteger)decodeData:(const uint8_t *)data size:(size_t)size timeStamp:(uint32_t)timeStamp;
44- (NSInteger)releaseDecoder;
45@end
46
47@implementation WK_RTCLocalVideoH264H265VP9Decoder {
48 RTCVideoDecoderH264 *m_h264Decoder;
49 RTCVideoDecoderH265 *m_h265Decoder;
50 RTCVideoDecoderVTBVP9 *m_vp9Decoder;
51}
52
53- (instancetype)initH264DecoderWithCallback:(webrtc::LocalDecoderCallback)callback {
54 if (self = [super init]) {
55 m_h264Decoder = [[RTCVideoDecoderH264 alloc] init];
56 [m_h264Decoder setCallback:^(RTCVideoFrame *frame) {
57 auto *buffer = (RTCCVPixelBuffer *)frame.buffer;
58 callback(buffer.pixelBuffer, frame.timeStampNs, frame.timeStamp);
59 }];
60 }
61 return self;
62}
63
64- (instancetype)initH265DecoderWithCallback:(webrtc::LocalDecoderCallback)callback {
65 if (self = [super init]) {
66 m_h265Decoder = [[RTCVideoDecoderH265 alloc] init];
67 [m_h265Decoder setCallback:^(RTCVideoFrame *frame) {
68 auto *buffer = (RTCCVPixelBuffer *)frame.buffer;
69 callback(buffer.pixelBuffer, frame.timeStampNs, frame.timeStamp);
70 }];
71 }
72 return self;
73}
74
75- (instancetype)initVP9DecoderWithCallback:(webrtc::LocalDecoderCallback)callback {
76 if (self = [super init]) {
77 m_vp9Decoder = [[RTCVideoDecoderVTBVP9 alloc] init];
78 [m_vp9Decoder setCallback:^(RTCVideoFrame *frame) {
79 auto *buffer = (RTCCVPixelBuffer *)frame.buffer;
80 callback(buffer.pixelBuffer, frame.timeStampNs, frame.timeStamp);
81 }];
82 }
83 return self;
84}
85
86- (NSInteger)decodeData:(const uint8_t *)data size:(size_t)size timeStamp:(uint32_t)timeStamp {
87 if (m_h264Decoder)
88 return [m_h264Decoder decodeData:data size:size timeStamp:timeStamp];
89 if (m_h265Decoder)
90 return [m_h265Decoder decodeData:data size:size timeStamp:timeStamp];
91 if (m_vp9Decoder)
92 return [m_vp9Decoder decodeData:data size:size timeStamp:timeStamp];
93 return 0;
94}
95
96- (void)setWidth:(uint16_t)width height:(uint16_t)height {
97 if (!m_vp9Decoder)
98 return;
99 [m_vp9Decoder setWidth:width height:height];
100}
101
102- (NSInteger)releaseDecoder {
103 if (m_h264Decoder)
104 return [m_h264Decoder releaseDecoder];
105 if (m_h265Decoder)
106 return [m_h265Decoder releaseDecoder];
107 return [m_vp9Decoder releaseDecoder];
108}
109@end

113class RemoteVideoDecoderFactory final : public VideoDecoderFactory {
114public:
115 explicit RemoteVideoDecoderFactory(std::unique_ptr<VideoDecoderFactory>&&);
116 ~RemoteVideoDecoderFactory() = default;
117
118private:
119 std::vector<SdpVideoFormat> GetSupportedFormats() const final;
120 std::unique_ptr<VideoDecoder> CreateVideoDecoder(const SdpVideoFormat& format) final;
121
122 std::unique_ptr<VideoDecoderFactory> m_internalFactory;
123};
124
125class RemoteVideoDecoder final : public webrtc::VideoDecoder {
126public:
127 explicit RemoteVideoDecoder(WebKitVideoDecoder);
128 ~RemoteVideoDecoder();
129
130private:
131 int32_t InitDecode(const VideoCodec*, int32_t number_of_cores) final;
132 int32_t Decode(const EncodedImage&, bool missing_frames, int64_t render_time_ms) final;
133 int32_t RegisterDecodeCompleteCallback(DecodedImageCallback*) final;
134 int32_t Release() final;
135 const char* ImplementationName() const final { return "RemoteVideoToolBox"; }
136
137 WebKitVideoDecoder m_internalDecoder;
138};
139
140struct VideoDecoderCallbacks {
141 VideoDecoderCreateCallback createCallback;
142 VideoDecoderReleaseCallback releaseCallback;
143 VideoDecoderDecodeCallback decodeCallback;
144 VideoDecoderRegisterDecodeCompleteCallback registerDecodeCompleteCallback;
145};
146
147static VideoDecoderCallbacks& videoDecoderCallbacks() {
148 static VideoDecoderCallbacks callbacks;
149 return callbacks;
150}
151
152void setVideoDecoderCallbacks(VideoDecoderCreateCallback createCallback, VideoDecoderReleaseCallback releaseCallback, VideoDecoderDecodeCallback decodeCallback, VideoDecoderRegisterDecodeCompleteCallback registerDecodeCompleteCallback)
153{
154 auto& callbacks = videoDecoderCallbacks();
155 callbacks.createCallback = createCallback;
156 callbacks.releaseCallback = releaseCallback;
157 callbacks.decodeCallback = decodeCallback;
158 callbacks.registerDecodeCompleteCallback = registerDecodeCompleteCallback;
159}
160
161RemoteVideoDecoder::RemoteVideoDecoder(WebKitVideoDecoder internalDecoder)
162 : m_internalDecoder(internalDecoder)
163{
164}
165
166RemoteVideoDecoder::~RemoteVideoDecoder()
167{
168 videoDecoderCallbacks().releaseCallback(m_internalDecoder);
169}
170
171void videoDecoderTaskComplete(void* callback, uint32_t timeStamp, CVPixelBufferRef pixelBuffer, uint32_t timeStampRTP)
172{
173 auto videoFrame = VideoFrame::Builder().set_video_frame_buffer(pixelBufferToFrame(pixelBuffer))
174 .set_timestamp_rtp(timeStampRTP)
175 .set_timestamp_ms(0)
176 .set_rotation((VideoRotation)RTCVideoRotation_0)
177 .build();
178 videoFrame.set_timestamp(timeStamp);
179
180 static_cast<DecodedImageCallback*>(callback)->Decoded(videoFrame);
181}
182
183int32_t RemoteVideoDecoder::InitDecode(const VideoCodec* codec_settings, int32_t number_of_cores)
184{
185 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_OK;
186}
187
188int32_t RemoteVideoDecoder::Decode(const EncodedImage& input_image, bool missing_frames, int64_t render_time_ms)
189{
190 uint16_t encodedWidth = 0;
191 uint16_t encodedHeight = 0;
192 if (input_image._frameType == VideoFrameType::kVideoFrameKey) {
193 encodedWidth = rtc::dchecked_cast<uint16_t>(input_image._encodedWidth);
194 encodedHeight = rtc::dchecked_cast<uint16_t>(input_image._encodedHeight);
195 }
196 return videoDecoderCallbacks().decodeCallback(m_internalDecoder, input_image.Timestamp(), input_image.data(), input_image.size(), encodedWidth, encodedHeight);
197}
198
199int32_t RemoteVideoDecoder::RegisterDecodeCompleteCallback(DecodedImageCallback* callback)
200{
201 return videoDecoderCallbacks().registerDecodeCompleteCallback(m_internalDecoder, callback);
202}
203
204int32_t RemoteVideoDecoder::Release()
205{
206 RegisterDecodeCompleteCallback(nullptr);
207 return 0;
208}

210RemoteVideoDecoderFactory::RemoteVideoDecoderFactory(std::unique_ptr<VideoDecoderFactory>&& internalFactory)
211 : m_internalFactory(std::move(internalFactory))
212{
213}
214
215std::vector<SdpVideoFormat> RemoteVideoDecoderFactory::GetSupportedFormats() const
216{
217 return m_internalFactory->GetSupportedFormats();
218}
219
220std::unique_ptr<VideoDecoder> RemoteVideoDecoderFactory::CreateVideoDecoder(const SdpVideoFormat& format)
221{
222 if (!videoDecoderCallbacks().createCallback)
223 return m_internalFactory->CreateVideoDecoder(format);
224
225 auto identifier = videoDecoderCallbacks().createCallback(format);
226 if (!identifier)
227 return m_internalFactory->CreateVideoDecoder(format);
228
229 return std::make_unique<RemoteVideoDecoder>(identifier);
230}
231
232std::unique_ptr<webrtc::VideoDecoderFactory> createWebKitDecoderFactory(WebKitH265 supportsH265, WebKitVP9 supportsVP9, WebKitVP9VTB supportsVP9VTB)
233{
234 auto internalFactory = ObjCToNativeVideoDecoderFactory([[RTCDefaultVideoDecoderFactory alloc] initWithH265: supportsH265 == WebKitH265::On vp9Profile0:supportsVP9 > WebKitVP9::Off vp9Profile2:supportsVP9 == WebKitVP9::Profile0And2 vp9VTB: supportsVP9VTB == WebKitVP9VTB::On]);
235 return std::make_unique<RemoteVideoDecoderFactory>(std::move(internalFactory));
236}

262int32_t decodeFrame(LocalDecoder localDecoder, uint32_t timeStamp, const uint8_t* data, size_t size)
263{
264 auto* decoder = (__bridge WK_RTCLocalVideoH264H265VP9Decoder *)(localDecoder);
265 return [decoder decodeData:data size:size timeStamp:timeStamp];
266}
